{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κάτοπτρον</b>, τό, <br /> <b>mirror</b>, κ. εἴδους χαλκός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 393, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 429, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τίς γὰρ κατόπτρῳ καὶ τυφλῷ κοινωνί; Comedy texts cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.30.6a; κ. ἀνδρομήκη 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.206S.; ἐν κατόπτρῳ.. κατιδεῖν εἴδωλα παρέχοντι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 71b; ὥσπερ ἐν κ. ἑαυτὸν ὁρῶν [prev. author] “Phdr.” 255d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ={μηλωτίς}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus cited in 1st c.AD: Erotianus Grammaticus (see. κατοπτήρ 11): _metaphorically_, εὖ γὰρ ἐξεπίσταμαι ὁμιλίας κ.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] companionship's true <b>mirror</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 839; ἡ Ὀδύσσεια καλὸν ἀνθρωπίνου βίου κ. 4th c.BC: Alcidamas Rhetor cited in 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1406b13; κ. φύσεος, of a wine-cup, Theopomp. Comedy texts 32.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—spelt <b>κάτροπτον</b> in <i>Attic dialect</i> Inscrr., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.1471.47, 1544.58 (4th c.BC), +others\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], and this form should be restored in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 414c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <b>κάθοπτρον</b> should perhaps be restored in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Annuario” 4/5.463. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G7975","accentedUnicode":"κάτοπτρον","shortDef":"a mirror","mediumDef":"a mirror","stepGloss":"a mirror","stepTransliteration":"katoptron","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}